tedMIB.name: tedMIB

TedAreaIdTC.name: TedAreaIdTC
TedAreaIdTC.description: The area identifier of the IGP. If OSPF is used to advertise LSA, this represents an ospfArea. If IS-IS is used, this represents an area address.

TedRouterIdTC.name: TedRouterIdTC
TedRouterIdTC.description: The router identifier. If OSPF is used to advertise LSA, this represents a Router ID. If IS-IS is used, this represents a System ID.

TedLinkIndexTC.name: TedLinkIndexTC
TedLinkIndexTC.description: The link identifier. If OSPF is used, this represents an ospfLsdbID. If IS-IS is used, this represents an isisLSPID. If a locally configured link is used, this object represents an arbitrary value, which is locally defined in a router.

tedTable.name: tedTable
tedTable.description: This table indicates multiple TED information, which has been supported by RFC 3630 and RFC 5305.

tedEntry.name: tedEntry
tedEntry.description: This entry contains TED information commonly utilized in both MPLS and GMPLS.

tedLinkInformationSource.name: tedLinkInformationSource
tedLinkInformationSource.description: This object indicates the source of the information about the TE link.

tedLocalRouterId.name: tedLocalRouterId
tedLocalRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, RFC 2328, Appendix C.1 OSPF for IPv6, RFC 5340, Appendix C.1 ISO10589, Section 7.1
tedLocalRouterId.description: This object represents the Router ID of the router originating the LSA. If OSPF is used to advertise LSA, this represents a Router ID. If IS-IS is used, this represents a System ID. Otherwise, this represents zero.

tedRemoteRouterId.name: tedRemoteRouterId
tedRemoteRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, RFC 2328, Appendix C.1 OSPF for IPv6, RFC 5340, Appendix C.1 ISO10589, Section 7.1
tedRemoteRouterId.description: This object indicates the router at the remote end of the link from the originating router. If OSPF is used to advertise LSA, this represents a Link ID in the Link TLV. If IS-IS is used, this represents a neighbor System ID defined in RFC 5305. Otherwise, this represents zero.

tedLinkIndex.name: tedLinkIndex
tedLinkIndex.reference: OSPF Version 2, RFC 2328, Appendix A.4.1, OSPF for IPv6, RFC 5340, Appendix A.4.2 ISO10589, Section 9.8
tedLinkIndex.description: This object indicates the link state identifier. If OSPF is used, this represents an ospfLsdbID. If IS-IS is used, this represents an isisLSPID. Otherwise, this represents a unique identifier within a node.

tedLinkInformationData.name: tedLinkInformationData
tedLinkInformationData.description: If tedLinkInformationSource has the value unknown(0), this object MUST contain a value of zeroDotZero. If tedLinkInformationSource has the value locallyConfigured(1), an implementation can use this object to supply the identifier of the corresponding row entry in the teLinkTable of TE-LINK- STD-MIB (RFC 4220), the identifier of the corresponding row in a local proprietary TE link MIB module, or the value of zeroDotZero. If tedLinkInformationSource has the value ospfv2(2) and ospfv3(3), an implementation can use this object to supply the identifier of the corresponding row entry in the ospfLocalLsdbTable (OSPFv2-MIB) and the ospfv3AreaLsdbTable (OSPFv3-MIB), or the value of zeroDotZero. If tedLinkInformationSource has the value isis(4), an implementation can use this object to supply the identifier of the corresponding row entry in the isisAreaAddr of ISIS-MIB (RFC 4444), or the value of zeroDotZero. If tedLinkInformationSource has the value other(5), an implementation can use this object to supply the identifier of the corresponding row entry in the local proprietary MIB module, or the value of zeroDotZero.

tedLinkState.name: tedLinkState
tedLinkState.description: This object represents the actual operational state of this TE link. For instance, if a row is created in the TED table, but the actual TE link is not available for some reason (e.g., when there is not yet a physical link or the link has been manually disabled), then the object would be down(2) state. In contrast, if a row is added and the TE link is available, this would be operationally up(1).

tedAreaId.name: tedAreaId
tedAreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, RFC 2328, Appendix C.2 OSPF for IPv6, RFC 5340, Appendix C.2 ISO10589, Section 9.8
tedAreaId.description: This object indicates the area identifier of the IGP. If OSPF is used to advertise LSA, this represents an ospfArea. If IS-IS is used, this represents an area address. Otherwise, this represents zero.

tedLinkType.name: tedLinkType
tedLinkType.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.1
tedLinkType.description: This indicates the type of the link, such as point to point or multi-access.

tedTeRouterIdAddrType.name: tedTeRouterIdAddrType
tedTeRouterIdAddrType.description: This object indicates the TE-Router ID address type. Only values unknown(0), ipv4(1), or ipv6(2) are supported.

tedTeRouterIdAddr.name: tedTeRouterIdAddr
tedTeRouterIdAddr.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.4.1 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 4.3
tedTeRouterIdAddr.description: This object indicates the TE-Router ID.

tedLinkIdAddrType.name: tedLinkIdAddrType
tedLinkIdAddrType.description: This object indicates the address type of the TE Link ID. Only values unknown(0), ipv4(1), or ipv6(2) are supported.

tedLinkIdAddr.name: tedLinkIdAddr
tedLinkIdAddr.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.2 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 4.3
tedLinkIdAddr.description: This indicates the Router ID of the neighbor in the case of point-to-point links. This also indicates the interface address of the designated router in the case of multi-access links.

tedMetric.name: tedMetric
tedMetric.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.5 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.7
tedMetric.description: This indicates the traffic engineering metric value of the TE link.

tedMaxBandwidth.name: tedMaxBandwidth
tedMaxBandwidth.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.6 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.4
tedMaxBandwidth.description: This indicates the maximum bandwidth that can be used on this link in this direction.

tedMaxReservableBandwidth.name: tedMaxReservableBandwidth
tedMaxReservableBandwidth.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.7 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.5
tedMaxReservableBandwidth.description: This indicates the maximum bandwidth that may be reserved on this link in this direction.

tedUnreservedBandwidthPri0.name: tedUnreservedBandwidthPri0
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri0.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.8 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.6
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri0.description: This indicates the amount of bandwidth not yet reserved at the priority 0.

tedUnreservedBandwidthPri1.name: tedUnreservedBandwidthPri1
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri1.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.8 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.6
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri1.description: This indicates the amount of bandwidth not yet reserved at the priority 1.

tedUnreservedBandwidthPri2.name: tedUnreservedBandwidthPri2
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri2.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.8 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.6
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri2.description: This indicates the amount of bandwidth not yet reserved at the priority 2.

tedUnreservedBandwidthPri3.name: tedUnreservedBandwidthPri3
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri3.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.8 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.6
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri3.description: This indicates the amount of bandwidth not yet reserved at the priority 3.

tedUnreservedBandwidthPri4.name: tedUnreservedBandwidthPri4
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri4.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.8 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.6
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri4.description: This indicates the amount of bandwidth not yet reserved at the priority 4.

tedUnreservedBandwidthPri5.name: tedUnreservedBandwidthPri5
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri5.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.8 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.6
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri5.description: This indicates the amount of bandwidth not yet reserved at the priority 5.

tedUnreservedBandwidthPri6.name: tedUnreservedBandwidthPri6
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri6.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.8 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, 3.6
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri6.description: This indicates the amount of bandwidth not yet reserved at the priority 6.

tedUnreservedBandwidthPri7.name: tedUnreservedBandwidthPri7
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri7.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.8 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.6
tedUnreservedBandwidthPri7.description: This indicates the amount of bandwidth not yet reserved at the priority 7.

tedAdministrativeGroup.name: tedAdministrativeGroup
tedAdministrativeGroup.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.9 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.1
tedAdministrativeGroup.description: This indicates the Administrative Group to which the link belongs. Since the value is a bit mask, the link can belong to multiple groups. This is also called Resource Class/Color.

tedLocalId.name: tedLocalId
tedLocalId.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.1 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.1
tedLocalId.description: This indicates the Link Local Identifier of an unnumbered link.

tedRemoteId.name: tedRemoteId
tedRemoteId.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.1 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.1
tedRemoteId.description: This indicates the Link Remote Identifier of an unnumbered link.

tedLinkProtectionType.name: tedLinkProtectionType
tedLinkProtectionType.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.2 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.2
tedLinkProtectionType.description: This object indicates the protection type of the TE link.

tedLocalIfAddrTable.name: tedLocalIfAddrTable
tedLocalIfAddrTable.description: This table contains the IP address information of a local TE link.

tedLocalIfAddrEntry.name: tedLocalIfAddrEntry
tedLocalIfAddrEntry.description: This entry contains the IP address information of the local TE link.

tedLocalIfAddrType.name: tedLocalIfAddrType
tedLocalIfAddrType.description: This object indicates the address type of the local TE link. Only values unknown(0), ipv4(1), or ipv6(2) have to be supported.

tedLocalIfAddr.name: tedLocalIfAddr
tedLocalIfAddr.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.3, Traffic Engineering Extensions to OSPF Version 3, RFC 5329, Section 4.3 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.4
tedLocalIfAddr.description: This object indicates the address of the local TE link.

tedRemoteIfAddrTable.name: tedRemoteIfAddrTable
tedRemoteIfAddrTable.description: This table contains the IP address information of a remote TE link.

tedRemoteIfAddrEntry.name: tedRemoteIfAddrEntry
tedRemoteIfAddrEntry.description: This entry contains the IP address information of the remote TE link.

tedRemoteIfAddrType.name: tedRemoteIfAddrType
tedRemoteIfAddrType.description: This object indicates the address type of the remote TE link.

tedRemoteIfAddr.name: tedRemoteIfAddr
tedRemoteIfAddr.reference: Traffic Engineering (TE) Extensions to OSPF Version 2, RFC 3630, Section 2.5.4, Traffic Engineering Extensions to OSPF Version3, RFC 5329, Section 4.4 IS-IS extensions for TE, RFC 5305, Section 3.3
tedRemoteIfAddr.description: This object indicates the address of the remote TE link.

tedSwCapTable.name: tedSwCapTable
tedSwCapTable.description: This table contains the GMPLS TED switching capability information.

tedSwCapEntry.name: tedSwCapEntry
tedSwCapEntry.description: This entry relates each TE link with its GMPLS TE switching capability information. If the MIB module deals with only OSPF- TE information, the value of each object related with GMPLS TE extensions should be null.

tedSwCapIndex.name: tedSwCapIndex
tedSwCapIndex.description: This index is utilized to identify multiple switching functions on a local or remote TE link according to definitions of textual conventions of GMPLS, RFC 4801.

tedSwCapType.name: tedSwCapType
tedSwCapType.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapType.description: This object indicates the GMPLS switching capability assigned to the TE link according to definitions of textual conventions of GMPLS, RFC 4801.

tedSwCapEncoding.name: tedSwCapEncoding
tedSwCapEncoding.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapEncoding.description: This object indicates the GMPLS encoding type assigned to the TE link.

tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri0.name: tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri0
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri0.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri0.description: This object indicates the maximum bandwidth of the TE link at the priority 0 for GMPLS LSP creation.

tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri1.name: tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri1
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri1.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri1.description: This object indicates the maximum bandwidth of the TE link at the priority 1 for GMPLS LSP creation.

tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri2.name: tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri2
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri2.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri2.description: This object indicates the maximum bandwidth of the TE link at the priority 2 for GMPLS LSP creation.

tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri3.name: tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri3
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri3.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri3.description: This object indicates the maximum bandwidth of the TE link at the priority 3 for GMPLS LSP creation.

tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri4.name: tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri4
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri4.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri4.description: This object indicates the maximum bandwidth of the TE link at the priority 4 for GMPLS LSP creation.

tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri5.name: tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri5
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri5.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri5.description: This object indicates the maximum bandwidth of the TE link at the priority 5 for GMPLS LSP creation.

tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri6.name: tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri6
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri6.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri6.description: This object indicates the maximum bandwidth of the TE link at the priority 6 for GMPLS LSP creation.

tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri7.name: tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri7
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri7.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapMaxLspBandwidthPri7.description: This object indicates the maximum bandwidth of the TE link at the priority 7 for GMPLS LSP creation.

tedSwCapMinLspBandwidth.name: tedSwCapMinLspBandwidth
tedSwCapMinLspBandwidth.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapMinLspBandwidth.description: This object indicates the minimum bandwidth of the TE link for GMPLS LSP creation if the switching capability field is TDM, PSC-1, PSC-2, PSC-3, or PSC-4.

tedSwCapIfMtu.name: tedSwCapIfMtu
tedSwCapIfMtu.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapIfMtu.description: This object indicates the MTU of the local or remote TE link.

tedSwCapIndication.name: tedSwCapIndication
tedSwCapIndication.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.4 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.3
tedSwCapIndication.description: This object indicates whether the interface supports Standard or Arbitrary SONET/SDH.

tedSrlgTable.name: tedSrlgTable
tedSrlgTable.description: This table contains the SRLG information of the TE link.

tedSrlgEntry.name: tedSrlgEntry
tedSrlgEntry.description: This entry relates each TE link with its SRLG information.

tedSrlgIndex.name: tedSrlgIndex
tedSrlgIndex.reference: OSPF Extensions in support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.3 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.4
tedSrlgIndex.description: This index is utilized to identify multiple SRLG values on a local or remote TE link. This object represents an arbitrary value, which is locally defined in a router.

tedSrlg.name: tedSrlg
tedSrlg.reference: OSPF Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 4203, Section 1.3 IS-IS Extensions in Support of GMPLS, RFC 5307, Section 1.4
tedSrlg.description: This object indicates the SRLG value assigned to a local or remote TE link.

tedStatusChangeNotificationMaxRate.name: tedStatusChangeNotificationMaxRate
tedStatusChangeNotificationMaxRate.description: A lot of notifications relating to the status change are expected to generate in a node, especially when a network failure occurs and might cause a performance degradation of the node itself. To avoid such a defect, this object provides the maximum number of notifications generated per minute. If events occur more rapidly, the implementation may simply fail to emit these notifications during that period, or may queue them until an appropriate time. A value of 0 means no throttling is applied and events may be notified at the rate at which they occur.

tedCreatedDeletedNotificationMaxRate.name: tedCreatedDeletedNotificationMaxRate
tedCreatedDeletedNotificationMaxRate.description: A lot of notifications relating to new registration in the TED table by receiving new TE link information or deletion of existing entries in the TED table are expected to generate in a node. This object provides the maximum number of notifications generated per minute.

tedStatusChange.name: tedStatusChange
tedStatusChange.description: This notification signifies that there has been change in the TE information of tedTable, tedLocalIfAddrTable, tedRemoteIfAddrTable, tedSwCapTable, and/or tedSrlgTable. For example, this should be generated when tedUnreservedBandwidth is changed to create or delete LSP using the registered TE link.

tedEntryCreated.name: tedEntryCreated
tedEntryCreated.description: This notification signifies that there has been new registration in the TED table by receiving new TE link information. For example, this should be generated when a new index (tedLinkIndex) is registered in the TED table.

tedEntryDeleted.name: tedEntryDeleted
tedEntryDeleted.description: This notification signifies that there has been deletion of an entry in the TED table. For example, this should be generated when one of the existing entries is deleted in the TED table.

tedModuleFullCompliance.name: tedModuleFullCompliance
tedModuleFullCompliance.description: Compliance statement for agents provides full support for the TED MIB.

tedModuleReadOnlyCompliance.name: tedModuleReadOnlyCompliance
tedModuleReadOnlyCompliance.description: Compliance requirement for implementations only provides read- only support for TED. Such devices can then be monitored but cannot be configured using this MIB module.

tedMainGroup.name: tedMainGroup
tedMainGroup.description: Collection of objects for TED management

tedObjectsGroup.name: tedObjectsGroup
tedObjectsGroup.description: The objects needed to implement notification.

tedNotificationGroup.name: tedNotificationGroup
tedNotificationGroup.description: This group is mandatory for those implementations that can implement the notifications contained in this group.

tedUnnumberedLinkGroup.name: tedUnnumberedLinkGroup
tedUnnumberedLinkGroup.description: The objects needed to implement the unnumbered links.

tedNumberedLinkGroup.name: tedNumberedLinkGroup
tedNumberedLinkGroup.description: The objects needed to implement the numbered links.

tedSwCapGroup.name: tedSwCapGroup
tedSwCapGroup.description: The objects needed to implement the TE links with GMPLS TE switching capability information.

tedSwCapMinLspBandwidthGroup.name: tedSwCapMinLspBandwidthGroup
tedSwCapMinLspBandwidthGroup.description: The objects needed to implement the minimum bandwidth of the TE link for GMPLS LSP creation.

tedSwCapIfMtuGroup.name: tedSwCapIfMtuGroup
tedSwCapIfMtuGroup.description: The objects needed to implement the MTU information of the local or remote TE link.

tedSwCapIndicationGroup.name: tedSwCapIndicationGroup
tedSwCapIndicationGroup.description: The objects needed to implement the indication of whether the interface supports Standard or Arbitrary SONET/SDH.

tedSrlgGroup.name: tedSrlgGroup
tedSrlgGroup.description: The objects needed to implement multiple SRLG values with GMPLS TE information.
